<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 15 at 11:23PM CDT until June 15 at 11:45PM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1145 PM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN PUSHMATAHA...WESTERN LATIMER AND SOUTHERN PITTSBURG
COUNTIES...
At 1122 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Krebs to 7 miles southeast of Wardville, moving
southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Hartshorne...
Krebs...                          Kiowa...
Savanna...                        Alderson...
Ashland...                        Higgins...
Haywood...                        Mcalester Regional Airport...
Dunbar...                         Blanco...
Haileyville...                    Pittsburg...
Gowen...                          Dow...
Bache...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
